						               													<description>Description (English):&amp;#10;Ophiusa: The land of a thousand rivers. It is a card game for all ages.&amp;#10;It consists of 54 cards that represent several of the most outstanding events of the society, culture and politics of Galicia. Although you do not need any prior knowledge of history to play.&amp;#10;Ophiusa, besides being an entertaining board game, also develops an important didactic work, which will help the players to organize chronologically their knowledge of history.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal is to get more points than the rest of the players. For this, you must form a timeline of events with cards grouped by color in groups of four cards (one for each color). Besides, get extra points with the province cards that serve as a bonus. To form this timeline, each player will add a card in the sense of clockwise.&amp;#10;The cover of the game, shows the logo and the Galician flag.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Description (Galician):&amp;#10;Ophiusa: A terra dos mil r&amp;iacute;os. &amp;Eacute; un xogo de cartas para t&amp;oacute;dalas idades.&amp;#10;Componse de 54 cartas que representan varios dos acontecementos m&amp;aacute;is destacados da sociedade, a cultura e a pol&amp;iacute;tica galega. A&amp;iacute;nda que non &amp;eacute; preciso ning&amp;uacute;n tipo de co&amp;ntilde;ecemento previo da historia para poder xogar.&amp;#10;Ophiusa, ademais de ser un entretido xogo de mesa, tam&amp;eacute;n desenrola unha importante labor did&amp;aacute;ctica, que axudar&amp;aacute; os xogadores a organizar cronoloxicamente os seus co&amp;ntilde;ecementos da historia.&amp;#10;O obxectivo do xogo &amp;eacute; conseguir m&amp;aacute;is puntos ca o resto dos xogadores. Para isto, deberase formar unha li&amp;ntilde;a temporal cos acontecementos das cartas agrup&amp;aacute;ndoas por cores en grupos de catro cartas (unha de cada cor). A maiores, conseguiremos puntos extra grazas &amp;aacute;s cartas de provincia que servir&amp;aacute;n de bonus. Para formar dita li&amp;ntilde;a temporal, cada xogador engadir&amp;aacute; unha carta no sentido das agullas do reloxo.&amp;#10;A portada do xogo, fusiona o logo coa bandeira de Galiza (a terra dos mil r&amp;iacute;os).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
